<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="222" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/978.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-01">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Chinese Government has reduced the amount of the proposed loan to
                                £10,000,000, expecting relaxation of supervision. The British
                                Minister informs me however that his Government refuses to relax the
                                conditions even for the reduced amount. Similar information as to
                                the attitude of the French Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>